President Biden delivered a speech at the Philadelphia Shipyard in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, discussing his administration's efforts to invest in America and promote clean energy. He highlighted the progress made in job creation, with over 13 million new jobs created across the country, including nearly half a million in Pennsylvania. Biden emphasized the importance of strengthening the middle class and unions in driving economic growth. He also addressed the issue of inflation, noting that wages for low-wage workers have increased at a faster pace in over two decades. The President highlighted the investment in clean energy, particularly offshore wind projects, and the creation of good-paying union jobs. He emphasized the commitment to building American-made products and supporting American manufacturing and shipbuilding. Biden also discussed the importance of infrastructure investment and announced various projects aimed at improving transportation and safety in Philadelphia. He concluded by expressing optimism about America's future and emphasizing the country's capacity to achieve great things when working together.